{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17637007","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17637007"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T18:36:34+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T18:36:34+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17621"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17621","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17621"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10335"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"71660"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10335","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10335"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17621"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"57156"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"4948"},{"type":"tags","id":"7748"},{"type":"tags","id":"7751"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"24178"},{"type":"contributions","id":"24181"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"71660","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/71660"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EIn a study of 400 medical students, 280 reported experiencing significant stress during their clinical rotations. The researchers calculated a 95% confidence interval of 0.60 to 0.80 for the proportion of students experiencing stress.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the interpretation of this confidence interval?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["60% to 80% of all medical students in the study reported stress","We can be 95% certain that 70% of medical students experience stress","We can be 95% confident that between 60% and 80% of the population of medical students experience stress","The true proportion of stressed medical students varies between 60% and 80%","95% of medical students experience stress levels between 60% and 80%"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe correct interpretation is that we can be \u003Cstrong\u003E95% confident that between 60% and 80% of the population of medical students experience stress\u003C/strong\u003E. This means if we repeated this sampling process many times, about 95% of the calculated intervals would contain the true population proportion.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe confidence interval provides a range of plausible values for the true population proportion, with 95% confidence that this interval contains the true value.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["A 95% confidence interval means if we repeated the sampling process many times, about 95% of intervals would contain the true population proportion.","The width of a confidence interval for a proportion depends on the sample size and the observed proportion.","Confidence intervals help assess the precision of sample estimates and should guide interpretation of research findings."],"references":["Sullivan LM. Essentials of biostatistics in public health. 3rd ed. Burlington (MA): Jones \u0026 Bartlett Learning; 2018.","Dawson B, Trapp RG. Basic \u0026 clinical biostatistics. 4th ed. New York: McGraw-Hill; 2004."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"57156"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17621"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"57156","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/57156"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-20T10:41:17+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-20T10:41:40+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10335